*** Golang Tools Integration ***

2016/10/10	v1.0.10
+ make it easier to use guru -- Thanks @jostyee
	1. make "build_packages" to be optional
	2. add "guru_use_current_package" for auto-config
	
2016/10/10	v1.0.9
+ Add alternative gocode for better autocomplete performance -- Thanks @jostyee
	1. go get -u -v github.com/mdempsky/gocode
	2(optional). Set the Golang config: "gocode_client_mode": true

2016/09/15	v1.0.8
+ Merge 2 PRs for better Re-name feature and README fix

2016/05/28	v1.0.7
+ Fix an issue: #issue13

2016/04/25	v1.0.6
+ Add "-srcdir" arguments for goimports -- Thanks @ottob
+ Replce "oracle" with "guru" since oracle is deprecated -- Thanks @ottob
+ Add the check for the installation of dependent go tools(goimports, guru, gorename...)
!!! Users must install guru through "go get golang.org/x/tools/cmd/guru"

2016/04/20	v1.0.5
+ Add error messages for oracle and gorename
+ Add Tips for auto-completion configuration to README

2016/04/17	v1.0.4
+ Add messages.json for showing the CHANGELOG autmatically
+ Add the "GOPATH/PATH" setting notice into README

2016/04/16	v1.0.3
+ Use golangconfig to replace the gotools_settings
+ Improve the performance, especially for auto-completion
- Remove the Gotools's Package-Settings menu item: replaced by the unified Golang settings
!!! Users must migrate the global and project-specific settings
	Please refer to the README and "ExamplePorject.sublime-project", "golang.sublime-settings"

